@startuml agent-routing
title Agent Routing And Execution Sequence

autonumber
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Monospace
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

actor "Slack User" as slack_user
participant "Slack" as slack
participant "Slack Conversations API" as slack_api

box "Google Cloud Project"
  participant "Slack Events Endpoint\nPOST /slack/events" as slack_events_endpoint
  participant "Mention Handler" as mention_handler
  participant "Message Handler" as message_handler
  participant "Agent Routing" as agent_routing
  participant "Slack Assistant" as slack_assistant
  participant "Specialist Agent" as specialist_agent
  database "Firestore\nthreads/{thread_ts}" as fs_threads
  participant "Vertex AI" as vertex_ai
end box

slack_user -> slack : Post a message in a channel or thread
alt Explicit agent invocation by mention
  slack -> slack_events_endpoint : app_mention event
  slack_events_endpoint -> mention_handler : Pass event payload
  mention_handler -> agent_routing : Build invocation\n(team, channel, thread, user text)
else Follow-up message in an active assistant thread
  slack -> slack_events_endpoint : message event
  slack_events_endpoint -> message_handler : Pass event payload
  message_handler -> fs_threads : Read thread state\n(agent_id, status)
  alt Thread has an active assistant conversation
    fs_threads --> message_handler : Existing agent_id and active status
    message_handler -> agent_routing : Continue with assistant\nwithout mention
  else No active agent conversation
    fs_threads --> message_handler : No active thread agent
    message_handler --> slack : No response
  end
end

agent_routing -> slack_api : Fetch full thread history\nvia Slack API (conversations.replies)
slack_api --> agent_routing : All thread messages\n(user posts + bot posts)
agent_routing -> slack_assistant : Execute with full thread context
slack_assistant -> vertex_ai : Choose direct reply\nor delegation
alt Specialist delegation needed
  slack_assistant -> specialist_agent : Delegate request
  specialist_agent -> vertex_ai : Execute specialist task
  vertex_ai --> specialist_agent : Specialist response
  specialist_agent --> slack_assistant : Slack-ready response
else Assistant replies directly
  vertex_ai --> slack_assistant : Direct response
end
slack_assistant --> agent_routing : Assistant output
agent_routing -> fs_threads : Persist active agent_id=`assistant`
agent_routing -> slack : Post reply to the thread
slack --> slack_user : Show agent response

note right of slack_assistant
Basic behavior:
the assistant reads all posts in the thread,
including user posts and bot posts,
and either answers directly or delegates to one specialist.
end note

note over agent_routing, fs_threads
The routing layer stores `assistant` on the thread
so later replies continue through the same public entrypoint.
end note

note over message_handler
Recommended guard conditions for message events:
- react only to user-authored messages
- ignore bot, edit, and delete related subtypes
- limit auto-replies to threads with an active agent conversation
end note

note over slack_api, slack_assistant
Context collection rule:
retrieve the full thread from Slack API,
including both user messages and bot messages,
before running the assistant.
end note

@enduml
